### Additional notes

I am still relatively new to Vapor so I am not sure if this is a Vapor issue or a swift-nio issue.

I am trying to run a local Vapor serving inside an iOS application to serve Protomaps "PMTiles" map tile databases located in the application's Documents folder. The basic conceit with PMTiles is to store all the map tiles in a single file and read them back out using HTTP range requests:

https://docs.protomaps.com/pmtiles/

The map tiles files are sufficiently large that I do not want to bundle them with the application itself. I have written a middleware component to do this and it seems to work as expected for smaller files that are typically < 100MB. I have included the code the middleware below.

For larger files (ranging from 100MB - 4GB) the application panics with this error:

```
NIOCore/ByteBuffer-core.swift:303: Fatal error: Unexpectedly found nil while unwrapping an Optional value
```

Specifically:

```
        @inlinable
        static func _allocateAndPrepareRawMemory(bytes: _Capacity, allocator: Allocator) -> UnsafeMutableRawPointer {
            let ptr = allocator.malloc(size_t(bytes))!
            // bind the memory so we can assume it elsewhere to be bound to UInt8
            ptr.bindMemory(to: UInt8.self, capacity: Int(bytes))
            return ptr
        }
```

I am unclear whether this is happening because the call `request.fileio.streamFile` does not account for HTTP range headers which are sent along with every request or whether something else is happening.

If it is the former, is there a more suitable method to call to accomplish this or do I need explicitly open, seek and the read the file contents parsing the Range header in the request?

Thanks,

```
import Vapor

enum DocumentFileURLKey: StorageKey {
	typealias Value = URL
}

struct DocumentsMiddleware: Middleware {
	private let basePath: String?

	init(basePath: String? = nil) { self.basePath = basePath }

	func respond(to request: Request, chainingTo next: Responder) -> EventLoopFuture<Response> {
		var path = request.url.path
		if let prefix = basePath, !prefix.isEmpty, path.hasPrefix(prefix) {
			path = String(path.dropFirst(prefix.count))
		}
		path = path.trimmingCharacters(in: CharacterSet(charactersIn: "/"))
		guard !path.isEmpty,
		      let fileName = path.split(separator: "/").last,
		      !fileName.isEmpty
		else {
			return request.eventLoop.makeFailedFuture(
				Abort(.notFound,
				      reason: "No file name could be derived from the request path.")
			)
		}
		guard let documentsURL = FileManager.default.urls(
			for: .documentDirectory,
			in: .userDomainMask
		).first else {
			return request.eventLoop.makeFailedFuture(
				Abort(.internalServerError,
				      reason: "Unable to locate the Documents directory.")
			)
		}

		let fileURL = documentsURL.appendingPathComponent(String(fileName))

		guard FileManager.default.fileExists(atPath: fileURL.path) else {
			return request.eventLoop.makeFailedFuture(
				Abort(.notFound,
				      reason: "File \"\(fileName)\" not found in Documents.")
			)
		}

		request.storage[DocumentFileURLKey.self] = fileURL

		print("STREEEEEM")
		return request.fileio.streamFile(at: fileURL.path, advancedETagComparison: true)
		// return next.respond(to: request)
	}
}

extension Application {

	func configure() throws {

		let corsConfiguration = CORSMiddleware.Configuration(
			allowedOrigin: .all,
			allowedMethods: [.GET, .OPTIONS],
			allowedHeaders: [.accept, .authorization, .contentType, .origin, .xRequestedWith, .userAgent, .accessControlAllowOrigin]
		)

		let cors = CORSMiddleware(configuration: corsConfiguration)
		self.middleware.use(cors, at: .beginning)
		self.middleware.use(DocumentsMiddleware())
	}
}

```

